      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison of FEA-predicted peak von Mises stress against strain gauge measurements using mean absolute percentage error (MAPE) metric. MAPE = 4.2% across all 18 test configurations (6 specimens × 3 loading conditions), within the pre-specified acceptance threshold of 10%. Statistical validation metric computed per ASME V&V 10.1 framework with Bayesian uncertainty propagation. U95 validation uncertainty = ±6.1%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
