      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-cou1-ortho-qoi-criteria",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is peak von Mises stress in the tibial tray keel region, directly linked to fatigue failure mechanism identified in post-market surveillance data. Secondary QoI is tibial plateau contact pressure distribution, relevant to polyethylene wear prediction. Both QoIs are directly measured in validation experiments and directly computed from FEA output without surrogate transformations. Clinical relevance established through literature review of tibial tray failure modes."
