      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-cou1-ortho-nse-criteria",
      "rationale": "Iterative solver convergence monitored via force and displacement residuals. Convergence criterion set at 1×10⁻⁶ (relative residual norm). Contact status convergence verified through Newton-Raphson iteration tracking. Round-off error assessed via double-precision arithmetic confirmation. Solver error contribution to total numerical error estimated at <0.1% via error decomposition analysis. Achieved level 3 exceeds MRL 3 requirement of level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-cou1-ortho-ue-criteria",
      "rationale": "FEA model developed by senior biomechanical engineer (10+ years FEA experience) with independent peer review by second qualified engineer. Simulation workflow documented in standard operating procedure SOP-FEA-ORTHO-003. Model setup checklist completed and signed for each simulation run. Independent model rebuild performed by second analyst to confirm reproducibility; peak stress results agreed within 0.4%. Use error controls documented in project quality plan."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-cou1-ortho-mf-criteria",
      "rationale": "Continuum linear elastic model with nonlinear frictional contact (Coulomb friction μ=0.04 for CoCr-UHMWPE interface per published tribology data) selected based on literature review of tibial tray modeling approaches. Bone modeled as transversely isotropic elastic material with CT-derived heterogeneous modulus distribution. Model form assumptions (small strain, quasi-static loading) justified by maximum principal strain <0.5% and loading rate analysis confirming quasi-static regime. Sensitivity analysis confirms model form error <5% relative to viscoelastic reference model."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-cou1-ortho-mi-criteria",
      "rationale": "Material properties sourced from peer-reviewed literature with traceability: CoCr alloy (ASTM F75, E=210 GPa, ν=0.30), UHMWPE (ISO 5834-2, E=0.94 GPa, ν=0.46), cortical bone (CT-derived Keyak-Falkinstein relationship, mean E=17.5 GPa). Geometric inputs from CMM-verified CAD model with dimensional tolerances ±0.02 mm. Boundary conditions derived from ISO 14243-1 force-moment profiles. Input uncertainty quantified via Monte Carlo analysis (n=1000 samples) with full covariance structure; 95th percentile stress response within acceptance threshold."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
