      "rationale": "Six cadaveric tibial specimens selected to span target population bone density range (T-score -0.5 to -2.5 per DXA screening). Specimen demographics: age 55-72, BMI 22-31, no prior knee surgery. Tibial trays implanted by experienced orthopaedic surgeon per standard surgical technique. Specimen characterization includes CT-based bone density mapping, geometry measurement, and pre-test radiographic confirmation of implant seating. Sample size justified by power analysis targeting 80% power to detect 10% stress difference."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
